text: Machecoul-Saint-Même is a commune. It is in the Pays de la Loire region in the Loire-Atlantique department in western France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Machecoul (the seat) and Saint-Même-le-Tenu.Arrêté préfectoral 23 November 2015 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Loire-Atlantique
title: Machecoul-Saint-Même
